<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="84" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,772,1590]" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,324,1060,1086]" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Forewing length: 
<specimenCount box="[538,559,1061,1087]" pageId="5" pageNumber="84" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
<quantity box="[568,693,1060,1087]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.15" metricValueMax="1.2" metricValueMin="1.1" pageId="5" pageNumber="84" unit="mm" value="11.5" valueMax="12.0" valueMin="11.0">11–12 mm</quantity>
, 
<specimenCount box="[707,728,1061,1087]" pageId="5" pageNumber="84" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
<quantity box="[738,863,1060,1087]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" metricValueMax="1.3" metricValueMin="1.1" pageId="5" pageNumber="84" unit="mm" value="12.0" valueMax="13.0" valueMin="11.0">11–13 mm</quantity>
. The males of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1862" box="[1037,1168,1060,1086]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Teulisna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chiloides">
<emphasis box="[1037,1168,1060,1086]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">T. chiloides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles to that of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Walker, 1862)" baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1862" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Teulisna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tumida">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">T. tumida</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Walker, F." box="[245,402,1096,1122]" pageId="5" pageNumber="84" pagination="82 - 145" refId="ref11439" refString="Walker, F. (1862) Catalogue of the Heterocerous Lepidopterous Insects collected at Sarawak, in Borneo, by Mr. A. R. Wallace, with Descriptions of New Species. Journal and Proceedings of the Linnean Society, Zoology, 6, 82 - 145 + 171 - 198. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1096 - 3642.1862. tb 00945. x" type="journal article" year="1862">Walker, 1862</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, but can be distinguished by the less pronounced central protrusion of the forewing costa, less visible costal black edge basal to the protrusion and uniformly straw coloured hindwing, without any marginal fuscous band as in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1862" box="[363,468,1168,1194]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Teulisna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tumida">
<emphasis box="[363,468,1168,1194]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">T. tumida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Further, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1862" box="[576,704,1168,1194]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Teulisna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chiloides">
<emphasis box="[576,704,1168,1194]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">T. chiloides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinct from another similar looking Bornean species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Holloway, 2001" authorityName="Holloway" authorityYear="2001" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Teulisna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pseudochiloides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">T. pseudochiloides</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Holloway, J. D." box="[286,463,1204,1230]" pageId="5" pageNumber="84" refId="ref9429" refString="Holloway, J. D. (2001) The Moths of Borneo: Part 7; Family Arctiidae: Lithosiinae. Malayan Nature Journal, Southdene Sdn Bhd., 297 pp., 8 pls." type="book" year="2001">Holloway, 2001</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
by its more yellow and less fawn colouration, less brownish suffusions on forewing and yellow hindwing without any suffusion, and by the presence of the subcostal comma-shaped black spot on forewing. In female of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1862" box="[296,425,1276,1302]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Teulisna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chiloides">
<emphasis box="[296,425,1276,1302]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">T. chiloides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the subcostal comma-shaped spot and central protrusion of the forewing costa are absent and the characteristic fuscous shade present along the forewing inner margin which is gradually diffused towards the tornus. In male genitalia, sacculus is typically rounded and broad, costal process is rounded and short, harpe is acute. Aedeagus is short and broad with vesica bearing two sets of typically long and strong cornuti.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="84" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,772,1590]" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,355,1420,1446]" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">Distribution:</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[363,472,1420,1446]" name="Indonesia" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">Indonesia</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[488,586,1420,1446]" country="Indonesia" name="Sumatera Utara" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">Sumatra</collectingRegion>
, Sumbawa, 
<collectingRegion box="[725,830,1420,1446]" country="Indonesia" name="Sulawesi Utara" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">Sulawesi</collectingRegion>
), 
<collectingCountry box="[851,954,1420,1446]" name="Malaysia" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
(Borneo), Peninsular 
<collectingCountry box="[1205,1308,1420,1446]" name="Malaysia" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Holloway, J. D." pageId="5" pageNumber="84" pagination="174 - 271" refId="ref9292" refString="Holloway, J. D. (1982) Taxonomic Appendix. In: Barlow, H. S. (Ed.), An Introduction to the Moths of South East Asia. The Malayan Nature Society, Kuala Lumpur, pp. 174 - 271." type="book chapter" year="1982">Holloway 1982</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Holloway, J. D." box="[221,281,1456,1482]" pageId="5" pageNumber="84" refId="ref9429" refString="Holloway, J. D. (2001) The Moths of Borneo: Part 7; Family Arctiidae: Lithosiinae. Malayan Nature Journal, Southdene Sdn Bhd., 297 pp., 8 pls." type="book" year="2001">2001</bibRefCitation>
), the Great Nicobar (present study).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="84" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,772,1590]" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,317,1492,1518]" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">Remarks:</emphasis>
With the present record, Indian 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1862" box="[672,766,1492,1518]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Teulisna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[672,766,1492,1518]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">Teulisna</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known by 12 species and it is the first ever documentation of this genus from Indian islands. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1862" box="[537,740,1528,1554]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Teulisna" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="84" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chiloides">
<emphasis box="[537,740,1528,1554]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="84">Teulisna chiloides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is purely a Sundanian species and is known to prefer tropical lowland dipterocarp rainforest habitats (
<bibRefCitation author="Holloway, J. D." box="[599,778,1564,1590]" pageId="5" pageNumber="84" refId="ref9429" refString="Holloway, J. D. (2001) The Moths of Borneo: Part 7; Family Arctiidae: Lithosiinae. Malayan Nature Journal, Southdene Sdn Bhd., 297 pp., 8 pls." type="book" year="2001">Holloway 2001</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
